                     <origDate notBefore="1850" notAfter="1906">Second half of the 19th – early 20th
                        cent.
 Additio 3 states that the Ms. was bought during the time of rās
                        Mangašā (Mangašā Yoḥannǝs, d. 1906) and rās Sǝbḥāt (Sǝbḥāt ʾAragāwi, d.
                        1914; received the title of rās in 1892; s. EAE IV, 587-589).</origDate>
                  </origin>
                  <provenance>The name of the original owner was erased,
                     but can still be read at some places as Walatta Samāʿt (s. <locus target="#58ra">58ra</locus>, 61va). Instead, other names were inserted:
                     Tasfā Ṣǝyon (<locus target="#46ra">46ra</locus>, 47va, 48vb, 49rb, 50rb),
                     Walatta Nob (<locus target="#47rc">47rc</locus>, 48rab, 48vc, 49rb, 49vb) and
                     Walda Madḫǝn (<locus target="#47va">47va</locus>, 49rb, 50rb, 51ra,
                     91ra).</provenance>
               </history>
